ers%20are%20less%20productive%20than%20their%20in-office%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20those%20thriving%20under%20remote%20work%2C%20firms'%20attempts%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-making-workers-employees-return-to-office-rto-wfh-hybrid-2023-1%5C%22%3Eorders%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20get%20everyone%20back%20in%20has%20come%20as%20an%20unpleasant%20shock.%20For%20Danielle%2C%20who%20was%20a%20manager%2C%20it%20also%20points%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-work-from-home-employees-better-boss-managers-ceo-2022-6%5C%22%3Efailures%20in%20managing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20early%20this%20year%2C%20Danielle%20left%20her%20old%20role%20for%20an%20all-remote%20job%20at%20a%20hybrid-first%20company.%20At%20that%20firm%2C%20the%20push%20isn't%20to%20get%20people%20into%20the%20office%2C%20but%20instead%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20stay%20in%20communication%20and%20be%20productive%20in%20a%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20tools%20are%20there.%20The%20ability%20is%20there.%20It%20is%20just%20whether%20or%20not%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20move%20into%20the%20new%20way%20of%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20with%20any%20big%20shift%2C%20in%20any%20social%20shift%2C%20you've%20got%20the%20people%20who%20just%20really%20want%20to%20hang%20onto%20the%20old%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20most%20insecure%20managers%20need%20to%20have%20eyes%20on%20their%20workers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20who%20have%20quit%20rather%20than%20returned%20to%20office%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-return-to-office-baby-boomer-never-wants-go-back-2023-4%5C%22%3Econtinually%20pointed%20fingers%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-return-to-office-quit-job-microm