not%20obtain%20critical%20components%20and%20manufacture%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.alarabiya.net%2FNews%2Fworld%2F2023%2F08%2F15%2FRussian-Kh-101-missiles-produced-this-year-sanctions-must-be-strengthened-Kyiv%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHe%2520stressed%253A%2520%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHead%20of%20the%20President's%20Office%20Andriy%20Yermak%20on%20Telegram.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Kazakhstan%20back%20door%20for%20tech%20supplies%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20sanctions%20include%20a%20ban%20on%20the%20sale%20of%20technology%20that%20could%20be%20used%20by%20Russia%20to%20build%20weapons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20armaments%20industry%20has%20long%20depended%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussias-microchips-search-hints-at-problem-for-us-chinese-militaries-2023-5%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3EUS%20microchip%20technology%20for%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20components%20such%20as%20the%20navigation%20systems%20for%20long-range%20missiles%2C%20as%20well%20as%20drones%20and%20planes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22912%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russo-Kazakhstan%20border%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dcd4a95e5d5a00195f2193%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22684%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECars%20(background)%20are%20seen%20queueing%20on%20the%20Russian%20side%20of%20the%20border%20with%20Kazakhstan%20near%20the%20Kazakh%20Syrym%20crossing%20point%20on%20September%2027%2C%202022.%3Cp%3ESTRINGER%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20Sommerville%2C%20an%20open-source%20intelligence%20investigator%20with%20the%20UK's%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20(RUSI)%2C%20authored%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.rusi.org%2FRUSI-Silicon-Lifeline-final-updated-web_1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20450%20foreign-made%20components%20were%20being%20used%20in%20Russia's%20most%20sophisticated%20weapons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Russia%20had%20adapted%20to%20the%20sanctions%20and%20built%20a%20successful%20covert%20procurement%20system%20centered%20in%20its%20neighbors%20and%20other%20nearby%20states%2C%20including%20Kazakhstan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20the%20initial%20sanctions%20and%20export%20control%20measures%20that%20were%20put%20in%20place%20just%20after%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20they%20have%20adapted%20and%20they're%20relying%20on%20these%20on%20these%20third%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20problem%20we've%20never%20faced%20before%2C%20at%20least%20not%20on%20this%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKazakhstan's%20Minister%20of%20National%20Economy%20Alibek%20Kuantyrov%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Insider%20said%20that%20though%20the%20country%20has%20not%20joined%20in%20Western%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%2C%20it%20was%20committed%20to%20slowing%20the%20flow%20of%20sanctioned%20goods.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Kazakh%20government%20has%20consistently%20affirmed%20its%20commitment%20to%20ensuring%20that%20the%20territory%20of%20Kazakhstan%20is%20not%20used%20to%20circumvent%20sanctions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20has%20put%20in%20place%20stringent%20rules%2C%20including%20strict%20monitoring%20of%20sanctioned%20goods.%20The%20authorities%20apply%20necessary%20control%20measures%20to%20prevent%20secondary%20sanctions%20risks.%20Kazakhstan%20is%20open%20and%20transparent%20in%20these%20matters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20chips%20for%20Russian%20missiles%20bought%20in%20bulk%20online%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Silverado%20Policy%20Accelerator%2C%20a%20US%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F04%2F18%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fus-russia-chips-sanctions.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Russia's%20chip%20imports%20declined%20sharply%20after%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20war%2C%20but%20climbed%20again%20as%20it%20diversified%20its%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20figures%20from%20the%20opposition%20group%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.4freerussia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F3%2F2023%2F01%2Ffrf-sanctions-web.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Free%20Russia%20Foundation%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20semiconductor%20imports%20to%20Russia%20increased%20from%20%241.8%20billion%20in%202021%20to%20%242.5%20billion%20in%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20obtain%20the%20parts%2C%20the%20Russian%20defense%20ministry%20set%20up%20a%20network%20of%20fake%20companies%20often%20registered%20in%20countries%20such%20as%20Kazakhstan%20and%20Armenia%2C%20said%20Sommerville%2C%20the%20RUSI%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20then%20obtain%20US%20tech%20in%20bulk%20through%20third-party%20retailers%2C%20and%20transport%20it%20back%20to%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColonel%20Mykola%20Danilyuk%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20officer%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Feurope%2F2023%2F07%2F27%2Fukraines-missile-cemetery%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20Economist%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%20that%20Russia%20was%20using%20online%20stores%20to%20import%20US%20chip%20systems%20used%20to%20control%20missiles.%20Many%20of%20the%20parts%20are%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3Bdual%20use%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20where%20an%20item%20has%20civilian%20as%20well%20as%20military%20applications%20%E2%80%94%20and%20so%20aren't%20covered%20by%20the%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20simply%20order%20them%20on%20Aliexpress%20and%20export%20them%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20suitcases%20from%20Kazakhstan%2C%26quot%3B%20Danilyuk%20told%20the%20publication.%20A%20spokesman%20for%20Aliexpress%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20search%20by%20Insider%20found%20the%20technology%20available%20on%20other%20online%20sale%20platforms%20such%20as%20Amazon%20and%20eBay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20eBay%20spokesman%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20abides%20by%20the%20laws%20of%20the%20countries%20it%20operates%20in%2C%20and%20observes%20relevant%20international%20sanctions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20transactions%20involving%20Russian%20addresses%20have%20been%20suspended%20since%20March%20of%202022.%20We%20continuously%20monitor%20new%20transaction%20trends%20and%20update%20our%20controls%20as%20appropriate%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20spokesman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Economist%20report%2C%20logic%20boards%20from%20California-made%20Altera%20Flex%20have%20been%20used%20in%20building%20the%20KH-100%20cruise%20missiles%20Russia%20has%20used%20in%20attacks%20on%20Ukrainian%20cities%20and%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20didn't%20suggest%20Altera%20Flex%20was%20breaking%20any%20rules.%20The%20company%20didn't%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESommerville%20said%20that%20complex%20global%20trade%20systems%20meant%20it%20is%20difficult%20for%20compliance%20officers%20at%20corporations%20to%20know%20where%20a%20product%20may%20end%20up.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it%20was%20unlikely%20more%20sanctions%20alone%20would%20cut%20off%20Russia's%20supply%20of%20American%20technology.%20Instead%2C%20he%20suggested%20increased%20coordination%20between%20governments%20and%20private%20companies%20to%20raise%20awareness%20of%20Russian%20supply%20routes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnything%20that%20can%20be%20done%20to%20even%20slow%20down%20Russia's%20ability%20to%20rebuild%20stockpiles%20would%20have%20a%20net%20benefit%20for%20the%20Ukrainian%20forces%20on%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-how-russia-gets-us-tech-cruise-missiles-despite-sanctions-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692698557000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dcbd8e4ef9f30019f7ef6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-how-russia-gets-us-tech-cruise-missiles-despite-sanctions-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20West%20has%20imposed%20sweeping%20tech%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20aimed%20at%20damaging%20its%20weapons%20programs%2C%20but%20it's%20found%20a%20workaround.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-how-russia-gets-us-tech-cruise-missiles-despite-sanctions-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Navya%3A%20I%20don't%20believe%20I%20am%20a%20youth%20icon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692698495000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102942870%2Cimgsize-41264.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fnavya-naveli-nanda-says-she-always-wanted-to-something-meaningful-i-dont-think-i-am-a-youth-icon%2Farticleshow%2F102942870.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102942870.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAmitabh%20Bachchan's%20granddaughter%2C%20Navya%20Naveli%20Nanda%2C%20has%20made%20a%20name%20for%20herself%20on%20social%20media%20and%20as%20a%20podcaster.%20Despite%20her%20family's%20involvement%20in%20showbiz%2C%20Navya%20sees%20herself%20as%20a%20regular%2025-year-old%20girl%20working%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20world.%20She%20aims%20for%20an%20equal%20society%20where%20all%20genders%20are%20respected%20and%20voices%20are%20heard.%20Navya%20recently%20completed%20a%2030-day%20road%20tour%20promoting%20equality.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fnavya-naveli-nanda-says-she-always-wanted-to-something-meaningful-i-dont-think-i-am-a-youth-icon%2Farticleshow%2F102942870.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CJI%20Faults%20Centre's%20Note%20on%20Courts'%20Conduct%20in%20Govt%20Cases%2C%20Says%20it%20Wants%20to%20Dictate%20Judicial%20Review%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F02154727%2FScreenshot-2022-11-02-at-3.45.44-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EChief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20has%20said%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20draft%20Standard%20Operating%20Procedure%20(SOP)%20concerning%20judicial%20conduct%20in%20government-related%20cases%20%E2%80%9Cread%20as%20if%20the%20Centre%20wants%20to%20dictate%20the%20exercise%20of%20judicial%20review%20by%20courts%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fcji-says-some-parts-of-draft-sop-on-judicial-conduct-in-govt-cases-read-as-if-centre-wants-to-chaperone-judicial-review%2Farticle67218803.ece%3Futm_source%3Deveningwrap%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DNewsletter%26pnespid%3DvatlGjpJK.gF1KHR.SXkFZOMohi0DIUqfOOinbJ29Bhm3NHpxKlibxGPW7WYUAcNfWRH8g_0%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20gone%20through%20your%20draft%20SOP%E2%80%A6%20There%20are%20some%20points%20which%20actually%20say%20how%20judicial%20review%20should%20be%20exercised%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20told%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20who%20represented%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20had%20come%20up%20with%20a%20five-page%20draft%20SOP%20last%20week%2C%20telling%20the%20judiciary%20to%20treat%20government%20officials%20summoned%20to%20court%20in%20various%20cases%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fcentres-draft-sop-wants-judiciary-to-treat-government-officials-summoned-to-court-more-congenially%2Farticle67202080.ece%5C%22%3Emore%20congenially%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C%2C%20particularly%20in%20contempt%20of%20court%20cases.%20The%20note%20says%20that%20government%20officials%20are%20being%20summoned%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cslightest%20of%20reasons%E2%80%9D%20while%20suggesting%20a%20set%20of%20sweeping%20proposals%20with%20regard%20to%20judicial%20proceedings%20in%20cases%20where%20the%20government%20is%20a%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20CJI%E2%80%99s%20comments%20on%20the%20draft%20SOP%20note%2C%20Mehta%2C%20for%20the%20government%2C%20sought%20to%20clarify%20that%20there%20is%20no%20intention%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20government%20to%20change%20the%20courts%E2%80%99%20power%20of%20judicial%20review.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20note%20in%20question%20only%20refers%20to%20how%20senior%20government%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20chief%20secretaries%2C%20are%20being%20summoned%20by%20courts%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cslightest%20reason%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20agreed%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20view%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20frame%20%E2%80%9Cbroad%20yardsticks%E2%80%9D%20on%20how%20government%20officials%20should%20be%20summoned%20by%20courts.%20He%20also%20concurred%20with%20the%20argument%20made%20in%20the%20draft%20SOP%20that%20there%20has%20to%20be%20a%20bar%20on%20the%20courts%20from%20summoning%20officials%20when%20the%20case%20is%20still%20pending%20an%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20note%20pointed%20to%20the%20way%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DPWqgfugVn1w%5C%22%3Ejudges%20pull%20up%20officers%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20not%20following%20a%20dress%20code%20while%20visiting%20courts.%20%E2%80%9CGovernment%20officials%20are%20not%20officers%20of%20the%20court%20and%20there%20should%20be%20no%20objection%20to%20their%20appearing%20in%20a%20decent%20work%20dress%20unless%20such%20appearance%20is%20unprofessional%20or%20unbecoming%20of%20her%2Fhis%20position%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20draft%20SOP%20sought%20to%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20said%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20restrict%20its%20order%20only%20to%20the%20aspect%20of%20issue%20of%20summons%20to%20government%20officials%2C%20and%20nothing%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20various%20issues%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20draft%20SOP%2C%20the%20government%20said%20courts%20should%20only%20prescribe%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbroad%20composition%E2%80%9D%20of%20its%20expert%20committees%20and%20leave%20modalities%2C%20including%20finding%20members%20for%20these%20committees%2C%20to%20the%20government.%20It%20may%20be%20recalled%20that%20the%20top%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadani-hindenburg-case-sc-to-form-probe-committee-rejects-names-proposed-by-centre%5C%22%3Ehad%20insisted%20on%20naming%20each%20member%20of%20the%20expert%20committee%3C%2Fa%3E%20chaired%20by%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Justice%20A.M.%20Sapre%20to%20look%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fwhy-has-the-adani-hindenburg-issue-become-a-matter-of-national-concern%5C%22%3EAdani-Hindenburg%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20note%20also%20said%20courts%20should%20give%20some%20leeway%20to%20the%20government%20with%20regard%20to%20guidelines%20in%20cases%20concerning%20public%20policy%20issues.%20The%20government%20said%20compliance%20with%20judicial%20orders%2C%20which%20involve%20%E2%80%9Ccomplex%20policy%20issues%E2%80%9D%2C%20would%20require%20time%20as%20well%20approval%20from%20ministries%20and%20consultation%20on%20a%20larger%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20note%20also%20goes%20on%20to%20underline%20that%20judges%20hearing%20contempt%20proceedings%20relating%20to%20their%20own%20orders%20would%20go%20against%20the%20principle%20of%20natural%20justice.%20Instead%2C%20it%20says%20those%20facing%20contempt%20proceedings%20should%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20ask%20for%20trial%20by%20another%20judge%2C%20and%20courts%20should%20not%20insist%20on%20a%20particular%20outcome%2C%20especially%20on%20matters%20concerning%20the%20executive%20domain.%20It%20should%20be%20seen%20if%20a%20judicial%20order%20is%20enforceable%20at%20all%20in%20contempt%20cases%2C%20the%20draft%20note%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20says%20the%20idea%20behind%20such%20a%20draft%20SOP%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccreate%20a%20more%20congenial%20and%20conducive%20environment%20between%20the%20judiciary%20and%20the%20government%E2%80%9D.%20It%20hopes%20that%20the%20draft%20SOP%20will%20help%20improve%20the%20quality%20of%20compliance%20of%20judicial%20orders%20by%20the%20government%20machinery%20as%20well%20as%20save%20time%20and%20resources%20for%20both%20the%20courts%20and%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692698405000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F02154727%2FScreenshot-2022-11-02-at-3.45.44-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcji-faults-centres-note-on-courts-conduct-in-govt-cases-says-it-wants-to-dictate-judicial-review%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Union%20government%20had%20come%20up%20with%20a%20five-page%20draft%20note%20on%20Standard%20Operating%20Procedure%20last%20week%2C%20telling%20the%20judiciary%20to%20treat%20government%20officials%20summoned%20to%20court%20in%20various%20cases%20'more%20congenially'