0priest.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20realised%20I%20like%20men%20and%20that%20duality%20set%20in.%20So%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20say%20anything%20about%20it%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20until%20I%20was%2019%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Navin%2C%20speaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavin%20first%20came%20out%20to%20his%20best%20friend%20Amit%2C%20who%20he%20knew%20since%20they%20were%2010.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20already%20knew%20each%20other%20very%20well%2C%20although%20we%20were%20never%20friends%20who%20spoke%20about%20personal%20stuff.%20So%2C%20when%20I%20came%20out%20to%20him%2C%20it%20was%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20fact.%20I%20just%20kind%20of%20came%20out%20to%20him%20and%20nothing%20changed%20after%20that%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20being%20gay%20is%20really.%20People%20who%20know%20you%2C%20know%20you%20for%20who%20you%20are.%20What%20gender%20you%20sleep%20with%20barely%20makes%20a%20difference%20to%20them%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20he%20was%2021%20and%20in%20his%20third%20year%20of%20college%2C%20he%20had%20come%20out%20to%20most%20of%20his%20friends.%20He%20says%20he%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20tell%20all%20his%20friends%20and%20acquaintances%20that%20he%20was%20gay%20because%20he%20had%20begun%20feeling%20left%20out%20from%20their%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20also%20wanted%20to%20chime%20in%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20when%20people%20would%20share%20weird%20notions%20of%20what%20gay%20people%20are%20with%20me.%20Listening%20to%20them%2C%20I%20found%20some%20of%20their%20notions%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F152754%2Fiit-madras-kaushik-section-377-supreme-court%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egay%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20hilarious.%20They%20had%20no%20idea%20about%20gay%20people%20and%20how%20we%20exist.%20That%20be